Finally, with all the prerequisite variables, we were able to calculate the first moment of area (Q) for the PLP on the radar chart by subtracting the centroidal distance (R) from the radius of a circle (C) that circumscribes the property space of the polygon (see Fig. 6), and multiplying the difference by the area (A) of the polygon:Fig. 6
